casebody.data:
In re Brunswick Manuf’g Co., (Mortgagees, Appellants; Receiver, Respondent.) (Supreme Court, General Term, Third Department. February 24, 1890.)

Argued before Learned, P. J., and Landon and Mayham, JJ.

No opinion. Order modified by striking out the word “directed,” and by requiring undertaking of $1,000 to secure costs.
